Sentencas: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) are environmentally efficient energy conversion devices, but are partially limited by the complicated fabrication procedure.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography

Sentencas: In this work, dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (8YSZ) ceramics were successfully realized through a DLP (digital light processing) stereolithography method and the electrolyte self-supported fuel cell was also tested at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography

Sentencas: The sintering behavior of the as-printed planar samples were investigated and a fully dense ceramic can be achieved at 1450 degrees C.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography

Sentencas: The total conductivity of the sintered 8YSZ can reach 2.18 x 10(-2)S cm(-1) at a test temperature of 800 degrees C, which is acceptable for practical application.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography

Sentencas: For the electrolyte self-supported fuel cell test, a power density of 114.3 mW cm(-2) can be achieved when Ni-8YSZ cermet and La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (ISM) were used as anode and cathode.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography

Sentencas: It was demonstrated that 3D printing is a promising processing technique to build up electrolyte self-supported SOFCs with desired structure for the future development.
Titulo: Dense 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte by DLP stereolithography
